The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for genomic sequence analysis, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of computer science and biology. Specifically, the paper focuses on visualization techniques for understanding how these models identify motifs in DNA sequences. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) due to the use of deep neural networks and visualization techniques. Additionally, the paper touches on the biological aspect of the topic, which could potentially fall under q-bio.GN (Genomics) and q-bio.QM (Quantitative Methods).
